      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"
      },
      "description": "The four key DORA metrics at a glance, aggregated across all releases in the lookback window (1 year).\n\n- **Release Gap**: Average days between upstream v*.*.* tags. Lower = more frequent delivery.\n- **Lead Time p50**: Median hours from a developer's first commit to PR merge. Measures development velocity.\n- **Failure Rate**: Percentage of merged PRs that led to a failure signal (patch release, revert, or downstream cherry-pick).\n- **MTTR p50**: Median hours from a broken release (.0) to its hotfix patch (.1/.2). Only shown when patch releases exist."
    },
